Package demos.traversals

Class BinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • demos.traversals.BinarySearchTree<T>
  • public class BinarySearchTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object

    BinarySearchTree is a simple container class of Comparables. It is likely going to be used in the second lecture, to illustrate some points about inorder traversal.

    Author:
    Jason

      • rangeSearch

        public java.util.Iterator<T> rangeSearch​(T min,
                                         T max)
                                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Performs a range search on the binary tree. The search is inclusive on both ends and is implemented recursively. If min and max are the same, search(Comparable) is called.
        Parameters:
        min - the left end of the range search.
        max - the right end of the range search.
        Returns:
        An Iterator that exposes the elements that satisfy the search in ascending order.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if min > max.

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Queries the BST for emptiness.
        Returns:
        true if, and only if, there are zero keys in the tree.
